This method lets you add feedback messages to multiple elements at one
time. These will be in addition to the feedback messages automatically
generated when you call [[Solar_Form::validate()]].

Note that this method works with feedback on **elements**; if you wish
to add feedback about the form itself, use the [[Solar_Form::$feedback]]
public property.

--------------------
Example
--------------------

{{code: php
    require_once 'Solar.php';
    Solar::start();

    $form = Solar::factory('Solar_Form');

    $elements = array(
        'name' => array (
            'type' => 'text',
            'label' => 'Your name:',
        ),
        'email' => array (
            'type' => 'text',
            'label' => 'Email address:',
        ),
    );    

    $form->setElements($elements);

    // for some reason, we want to one feedback message on the 'name',
    // and two messages on the 'email'.
    $feedback = array(
        'name' => 'You really should type in your name.',
        'email' => array(
            'Be sure to type in your email.',
            'And make it a real one, no fakes!'
        ),
    );

    $form->addFeedback($feedback);
}}

If you set the elements as part of an array, you will need to make sure
the feedback is set as part of the same array. For example:

{{code: php
    $form->setElements($elements, 'contact');
    $form->addFeedback($feedback, 'contact');
}}

Of course, you can skip all this if you like and add the feedback
directly as part of the element to begin with:

{{code: php
    $elements = array(
        'name' => array (
            'type' => 'text',
            'label' => 'Your name:',
            'feedback' => array(
                'You really should type in your name.',
            ),
        ),
        'email' => array (
            'type' => 'text',
            'label' => 'Email address:',
            'feedback' => array(
                'Be sure to type in your email.',
                'And make it a real one, no fakes!',
            ),
        ),
    );    
}}